<worksheet >
    <title>FUN-1 Vector Operations and Applications</title>
  <introduction>
    <p>To earn an M on this outcome, you will need to correctly complete all three 
        parts; to earn a P on this outcome, you will need to correctly complete 
        two parts.</p>
  </introduction>  
  <page>
    <exercise workspace="1.5in">
        <introduction><p>Let <m>\vec{u}=\langle 1,-3,2\rangle, \vec{v}=\langle 4,0,-1\rangle,</m> 
            and <m>\vec{w}=\langle -1,1,2\rangle</m></p></introduction>
      <task><statement><p>Find <m>3\vec{u}\cdot(4\vec{v}-2\vec{w})</m></p></statement></task>
      <task><statement><p>Find the vector in the direction of <m>\vec{u}</m> with length of 
        <m>5\vec{v}</m>.</p></statement></task>
    </exercise>
    <exercise workspace="1.5in">
      <statement><p>A mechanic applies a force vector <m>\vec{F} = \langle 0,30,10 \rangle</m> 
        Newtons to the end of a wrench.  The wrench extends from the bolt at the origin, to a 
        position vector <m>\vec{r}=\langle 0.2, 0.4, 0 \rangle</m>. Find the resulting torque 
        vector <m>\vec{\tau}=\vec{r}\times\vec{F}</m> applied to the bolt.</p></statement>
    </exercise>
  </page>
</worksheet>